&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Theatre Practitioners&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trauma and Orthopaedics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;University Hospitals Dorset&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For this post you will be based at Poole Hospital &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 Vacancies: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operating Department Practitioners or Registered Nurses &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;University Hospitals Dorset are working to develop an expanded service for the Dorset community and wider areas. Poole is a great place to live and work where patient care and staff welfare are our top priorities. We are located in Poole town centre near the coast and New Forest. All this is on offer to any nursing and theatre practitioners making their next career move.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At this exciting time, are you what we are looking for?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With the new management team in place and focus on quality, transformation and service development, we are increasing our operating theatre suite and are looking for motivated people, to join our expanding theatre department to enhance the trauma and orthopaedic teams supporting the demand&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer great opportunities with an extensive educational program, to include the development of Surgical First Assistants (SFA), Anaesthetic Practitioners, leadership and management development to name but a few.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We pride ourselves on our friendly working environment and our desire to lead on Best Practice in the Operating Theatre setting. If you have the knowledge, skills, experience and drive that we are looking for to join our friendly and supportive team, then Poole and Royal Bournemouth theatres is the place for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working with multi-professional colleagues in a busy theatre department, you will be flexible and have experience of working in an operating theatre setting, but not essential. there are a number of specialities including; head and neck, gynaecology, general surgery, paediatric day case surgery, vascular, urology , anaesthetics and recovery– and you will become a valued member of our team. We encourage dual or multi-skilled practitioners, however full training will be given to facilitate development. Your peers, anaesthetists, surgeons and senior staff will support you to learn new skills and to expand your practice&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be either a:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered Operating Department Practitioner, Registered Nurse or Registered Nurse with a recognised anaesthetic course , who has recent experience across a range of different specialities. Experience of working in more than one area (scrub, recovery, or anaesthetic assistance will be an advantage).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Newly qualified&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note: if this job requires you to have a DBS check to enable you to properly fulfil the requirements of the job, on appointment you will be required to repay the cost of obtaining a DBS check and this amount will be reclaimed from your salary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 11/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provisional interview date: week commencing 23/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;INFORMAL VISITS ARE MOST WELCOME AND ENCOURAGED&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details or to arrange a visit please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clinical Team Manager: Jennifer Miller&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;e-mail: Jennifer.miller@uhd.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
